text: Sebastiscus marmoratus (Sea ruffe or False kelpfish) is a species of fish in the rockfish family found in the Western Pacific from southern Japan to the Philippines. It has also been sighted twice in Australia; once in Sydney Harbour in 1980 by naturalist Rudie Kuiter and in 2019 in Port Adelaide's inner harbour.
